{
  "texts": [
    "If Q1,…,QN are the amounts that a given entity receives from each of its N direct suppliers, and Q'1,…,Q'N are the transaction amounts that the model predicts, it specifically is assumed that ΔQ1,…,ΔQN follows a multivariate normal distribution with zero mean and covariance matrix D where ΔQi = Q'i -Qi. for i = 1,…,N.",
    "Following the methodology presented in 21, the authors' method outputs N + 1 different combinations of ΔQ1,…,ΔQN that would predict the receiving entity achieving an L gain or loss.",
    "For each time a reverse stress test is run, all entities were equally weighted to not inadvertently prioritize certain entities over others.",
    "In other words, a target entity is willing to receive goods from anyone who can provide it.",
    "Other weights can be used, if desired."
  ]
}